        <num>CC 609</num>
        <heading>609.  Termination of legacy of revenues</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 609.  Termination of legacy of revenues.
A legacy of revenues from specified property is a kind of usufruct and terminates upon death of the legatee unless a shorter period has been expressly stipulated.</p>
        </content>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=110803</p>
